cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.IT, cs.SE, cs.NI

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it discusses a method of exfiltrating data from secure and air-gapped computers. It could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves the use of USB devices and their potential security implications. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the transmission of binary data through electromagnetic emissions. It could also be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it presents a software solution for utilizing an unmodified USB device as a transmitter. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it involves the transmission of data through a covert channel.
